      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BANKER'S EMPEROR (3) resumed over 1200m at this track last time out and finished second, beaten 0.8 lengths. Unbeaten in three starts when second-up and will strip much fitter for this. Should feature in the finish. POPEYETHESAILORMAN (4) lines up for the first time since September 28. Started the last campaign in good style when in the placings over 1200m at this track, bringing the first-up record to two wins and two placings from seven starts. Now under the care of new trainer Richard Lines. One of the key contenders. PACIFIC HERO (9) improved sharply on his eighth two starts back with a win over 1020m at this track three weeks ago, getting home by 1.5 lengths after being in the firing line on the corner. One of the genuine hopes in the race. CHEVAL PEGASUS (8) had been in great form winning three on end before finishing third last time out over 1200m at this track. Must be considered.",
